   · Failure Trigger Summary: What went wrong and why (if failure).
   · Comparative Insight: Key difference from similar success/failure.
2. Variational Bottleneck Encoder: A 2-layer MLP takes concatenated embeddings of summaries and outputs a Gumbel-Softmax distribution over a discrete codebook $\mathcal{C} \in \mathbb{R}^{512 \times d}$. The encoder is trained offline on 10K MIA trajectories using the weighted IB loss (Eq. 3.3).
3. Storage: Compressed code $z$, summaries, outcome $Y$, surprise score, and a pointer to the Graph-of-Trajectories (GoT) structure are stored in a FAISS index.

