Chapter 4: Mathematical Analysis and Theoretical Guarantees

This chapter provides a rigorous mathematical analysis of the StratMem Agent framework. Building upon the theoretical foundations established in Chapter 3, we prove the core theorems governing the system's behavior. The chapter is organized into five sections: (1) existence, uniqueness, and convergence of the failure-aware Information Bottleneck encoder, (2) information-geometric properties of the hybrid cognitive retriever, (3) stability analysis of the MaTTS self-evolution loop with TPO-ES updates, (4) complete proofs of the Fisher-Rao/Bhattacharyya drift certificates, and (5) analytical bounds on the Memory Efficiency Ratio (MER). All results are presented as formal theorems with complete proofs.

